reporting-org.narrative: New Zealand Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade

description.narrative: MFAT provides development funding to Samoa for a number of activities within it’s Pacific agricultural programme. One of these programmes is for activities to increase the value and volume of Samoan cocoa export and increase financial returns for smallholder cocoa growers through increased investment and sustainable production and quality management. The Samoa Cocoa Industry Development Initiative commenced July 2017 through to June 2022.
